sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539281
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: rbs+crtZ(beta-carotene hydroxylase) under heat sensitive cI regulater
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: crtZ coding sequences come from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) (Accession number D90087)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains crtZ, which works as the zeaxanthin biosynthesis pathway when add beta-carotene as a substrate. crtZ is regulated by cI and cI regulated promoter. The promoter has two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This operon is under a heat sensitive cI QPI with a high promoter preceding the repressor (BBa_J23114).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rbs+crtZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: crtZ (beta-carotene hydroxylase) from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087. Part of the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway. Converts beta-carotene to the yellow pigment zeaxnathin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was made as a single biobrick rather than separate rbs and coding sequence, hence the use of blunt combination to generate the final sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K098995
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: heat sensitive cI QPI with high promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PGW7 plasmid and various BioBricks parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a heat sensitive cI QPI with a high promoter preceding the repressor (BBa_J23114). It can be used to construct a heat-inducible system if a reporter or indicator is adding to the right of this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
This is a mutagenized form because the original product had an extra PstI site between the repressor and terminator. While there are still extra basepairs between the end of the repressor sequence and the Biobricks scar, they no longer code for a PstI site.
The extra base pairs are: [repressor coding region] CTCCAGCGGCCGC [Biobricks scar]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Harvard iGEM 08

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742156
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Native ribosome binding site for crtZ (beta-carotene hydroxylase) from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: A virtual part to be added to the coding sequence blunt (without a scar).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742157
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding sequence for crtZ (beta-carotene hydroxylase) from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087. Part of the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway. Converts beta-carotene to the yellow pigment zeaxanthin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K098998
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of the part is the PGW7 plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the temperature sensitive cI coding region from the PGW7 plasmid. It was taken from the plasmid via PCR, and a RBS was also added (BBa_B0034). There is no scar between the RBS and cI coding region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Obtained by PCR. RBS added by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Harvard iGEM 08

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from luxICDABEG operon terminator of Vibrio fischeri <genbank>AF170104</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Bidirectional transcriptional terminator consisting of a 22 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In the naturally-occuring sequence there is a mismatch in the stem of the stem loop. This can be corrected via an A->G mutation (at position 40 -- sequence coordinate/not MFOLD coordinate). The above sequence does not reflect this mutation (but the MFOLD image does). This terminator's location cannot be found using some inverted repeat detectors like PALINDROME because it is too short and contains a mismatch. This one was found with the help of Tom Knight. It lies between two coding regions that point towards eachother.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cI regulated promoter is based on the pR promtoer from bacteriohage lambda. The promoter has two two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription. The specific sequence used here is based on the cI repressible promoter used in the Elowitz repressilator (and references therein).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
In order to address concerns about the promoter transcribing in the reverse direction, we have removed the -35 and -10 signals responsible for the promoter activity in the reverse direction. (More details needed here! DE, 2/24/03)

Incompatible with host expressing cI repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K098997
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This it the temperature sensitive cI from the PGW7 plasmid. It has the Elowitz RBS in front (BBa_B0034). It produces a temperature sensitive cI repressor that loses binding efficiency with the cI promoter between 35 and 42 degrees C.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Obtained by PCR. RBS also added by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Harvard iGEM 08
